<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Richmond Cycling Campaign (CYS0131)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Written evidence from</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> Richmond Cycling Campaign (CYS0131)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">To simply answer your key questions:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">1.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Is cycling safe?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">All the statistics tell me cycling is safe, and that’s what I tell our members. But this reflects only cycling as it is carried out today. In </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt; font-style:italic">every school in Richmond</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">, many more children </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt; font-weight:bold">want</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> to cycle to school than currently do so. What’s holding them bac</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">k? In general, it’s safety: no parent would allow a primary school child to cycle in a cycle lane on an A-road or A-road equivalent – when asked, parents generally list safety concerns as the reason for them not allowing children to get on a bike to school</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">My daughter wants to cycle to school, and is capable of making the journey, but I can’t allow her to ride in the gutter with cars, trucks and vans passing by a foot away at up to 30 mph. The only way to make cycling both *seem* and *be* safe for these ve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">ry vulnerable transport users is to provide safe places to cycle where they are not required to interact constantly with dangerous vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">What can central / local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Govt</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> do to improve cycling safety …</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Government across the country needs to provid</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">e safe, continuous, direct routes which make it possible for people to get on their bikes without the need for expensive lighting or clothing: in countries where lots of people cycle, it happens because they can do it without having to continuously interac</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">t with motor vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">We’ve tried, for too long, telling people how useful it is to get training, or legislating for safer HGVs, or making cars nicer for when they inevitably drive into people or things. Now let’s try the thing that we know – from plentif</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">ul evidence in Cambridge, as well as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Assen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">, from Bristol and from Copenhagen – cycling is something everyone can do, if we give them somewhere nice to do it.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">3.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Is it desirable / feasible to separate cyclists from other road users, including prohibit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">ing HGVs in peak hours …</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Prohibiting HGVs in rush hour isn’t going to make a primary school child any safer on an ordinary urban or sub-urban road: she still has to interact with buses, vans and cars in our current environment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Cycling in the UK is a safe </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">thing to do. However, most people rightly perceive:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">A vehicle squeezing by at much higher speed</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">Having to ‘own the lane’ in front of a vehicle weighing a ton or more</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">The intimidation of other road users who fail to see them</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">The dangerous behaviour of road users who don’t understand the highway code</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:7pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">And, most frequently, the minor inattentions that might result in a small scratch to another vehicle but potential death or serious injury to a cyclist</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">As th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt">ings that make them feel cycling is too dangerous or just isn’t worth it. No amount of telling people ‘cycling is safe’ will fix these things, but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt; font-style:italic">building somewhere safe to cycle</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11.5pt"> will do. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span><br /><br /><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>